{
  "texts": [
    "In this section, we explain why English-only preference tuning can reduce toxicity in model generations across multiple languages using probes, causal intervention, and neuron activation analysis.",
    "We adopt the residual stream perspective of transformer blocks (Elhage et al., 2021) and the framework of MLPs being key-value memory retrieval systems (Geva et al., 2021).",
    "The residual stream, also known as embedding, for a token at layer ℓ, denoted as x ℓ i ∈ R d, is propagated through residual connections (He et al., 2016).",
    "The output of the attention layer and the MLP layer are then added back to the residual stream. foot_2",
    "The additive nature of the residual stream view allows us to evaluate the contribution of different components separately."
  ]
}